ves the <code>_queue_reduction</code> code from Python to C++. It is stacked on top of <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"343803537\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/9729\" data-hovercard-type=\"pull_request\" data-hovercard-url=\"/pytorch/pytorch/pull/9729/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/9729\">#9729</a> and <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"344285738\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/9805\" data-hovercard-type=\"pull_request\" data-hovercard-url=\"/pytorch/pytorch/pull/9805/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/9805\">#9805</a>.</p>\n<p>For this PR I had to do some more work:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Move <code>nccl::reduce</code> from <code>python_nccl.cpp</code> into <code>nccl.{h,cpp}</code></li>\n<li>Rewrite the <code>queue_reduction</code> function.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>I also made a helper to convert <code>py::object</code> to a vector of <code>at::cuda::CUDAStream</code>, because there were now two places where we needed this.</p>\n<p><a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=4583066\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/apaszke\">@apaszke</a> <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=8120856\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/teng-li\">@teng-li</a> <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=9845\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/pietern\">@pietern</a></p>", "body_text": "This PR moves the _queue_reduction code from Python to C++. It is stacked on top of #9729 and #9805.\nFor this PR I had to do some more work:\n\nMove nccl::reduce from python_nccl.cpp into nccl.{h,cpp}\nRewrite the queue_reduction function.\n\nI also made a helper to convert py::object to a vector of at::cuda::CUDAStream, because there were now two places where we needed this.\n@apaszke @teng-li @pietern", "body": "This PR moves the `_queue_reduction` code from Python to C++. It is stacked on top of #9729 and #9805.\r\n\r\nFor this PR I had to do some more work:\r\n1. Move `nccl::reduce` from `python_nccl.cpp` into `nccl.{h,cpp}`\r\n2. Rewrite the `queue_reduction` function.\r\n\r\nI also made a helper to convert `py::object` to a vector of `at::cuda::CUDAStream`, because there were now two places where we needed this.\r\n\r\n@apaszke @teng-li @pietern "}